                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#18v #87v #90v" facs="019 088 091">Fols. 18v, 87v, 90v</locus>
                    <desc>lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#90v" facs="091"> f. 90v, line 7</locus>
                    <desc>lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#121v" facs="122"> line 3</locus>
                    <desc>words of text are written in the upper margin with symbol (+) marking the location the text is to be inserted</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#44v #58v #79r #80v" facs="045 059 080 081">Fols. 44v, 58v, 79r, 80v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., erasure markings are visible</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <locus target="#27r #49v #61v #64r #66r" facs="027 050 062 064 066">Fols. 27r, 49v, 61v, 64r, 66r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e11">
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
